data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","output_index":1,"item_id":"msg_tmp_6b4qtboowum","content_index":0,"text":"Tokyo's population varies depending on how you measure it:\n\n**Greater Tokyo Area (Metropolitan Region):**\nAccording to multiple sources, the Greater Tokyo Area population in 2026 is approximately **36.9 million**:\n- Macrotrends: 36,954,000 (metro area population in 2026)\n- World Population Review: 36,953,600 (2026 estimate)\n- Wikipedia/UN: 36,954,512 (2026 estimate)\n\nThis makes Tokyo the **most populous metropolitan area in the world**.\n\n**Tokyo Metropolis (Prefecture-level):**\nThe Tokyo Metropolitan Government's official estimate for January 1, 2026 shows **14,270,748 people**.\n\n**Tokyo's 23 Wards (City Proper):**\nThe historic city core has approximately **9-9.5 million residents**.\n\nThe slight population decline (about -0.22% annually) reflects a broader demographic trend in Japan of slowing growth and an aging population. [macrotrends.net](https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/cities/21671/tokyo/population) [worldpopulationreview.com](https://worldpopulationreview.com/cities/japan/tokyo) [en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greater_Tokyo_Area) [www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp](https://www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/information/press/2026/01/2026012906)","logprobs":[],"sequence_number":596}

data: {"type":"response.content_part.done","output_index":1,"item_id":"msg_tmp_6b4qtboowum","content_index":0,"part":{"type":"output_text","text":"Tokyo's population varies depending on how you measure it:\n\n**Greater Tokyo Area (Metropolitan Region):**\nAccording to multiple sources, the Greater Tokyo Area population in 2026 is approximately **36.9 million**:\n- Macrotrends: 36,954,000 (metro area population in 2026)\n- World Population Review: 36,953,600 (2026 estimate)\n- Wikipedia/UN: 36,954,512 (2026 estimate)\n\nThis makes Tokyo the **most populous metropolitan area in the world**.\n\n**Tokyo Metropolis (Prefecture-level):**\nThe Tokyo Metropolitan Government's official estimate for January 1, 2026 shows **14,270,748 people**.\n\n**Tokyo's 23 Wards (City Proper):**\nThe historic city core has approximately **9-9.5 million residents**.\n\nThe slight population decline (about -0.22% annually) reflects a broader demographic trend in Japan of slowing growth and an aging population. [macrotrends.net](https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/cities/21671/tokyo/population) [worldpopulationreview.com](https://worldpopulationreview.com/cities/japan/tokyo) [en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greater_Tokyo_Area) [www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp](https://www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/information/press/2026/01/2026012906)","annotations":[{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/cities/21671/tokyo/population","title":"Tokyo, Japan Metro Area Population (1950-2026) - Macrotrends","start_index":0,"end_index":0},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://www.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/information/press/2026/01/2026012906","title":"「東京都の人口（推計）」の概要（令和8年1月1日現在）|1月|都庁総合ホームページ","start_index":0,"end_index":0},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://worldpopulationreview.com/cities/japan/tokyo","title":"Tokyo Population 2026","start_index":0,"end_index":0},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greater_Tokyo_Area","title":"Greater Tokyo Area - Wikipedia","start_index":0,"end_index":0},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo","title":"Tokyo - Wikipedia","start_index":0,"end_index":0}],"logprobs":[]},"sequence_number":597}

data: {"type":"response.reasoning_text.done","output_index":0,"item_id":"rs_tmp_r13m90cswje","content_index":0,"text":"The user is asking about the current population of Tokyo. Based on the web search results, I can provide information about Tokyo's population from different sources and definitions.\n\nFrom the search results:\n1. Macrotrends: The metro area population of Tokyo in 2026 is 36,954,000, a 0.22% decline from 2025.\n2. World Population Review: Tokyo's 2026 population is estimated at 36,953,600, with a decrease of -82,600 residents over the past year, marking an annual decline of -0.22%.\n3. Wikipedia (Greater Tokyo Area): As of 2026, the United Nations estimates the total population at 36,954,512.\n4. Tokyo Metropolitan Government: The population of Tokyo Metropolis (the prefecture-level entity) as of January 1, 2026 is 14,270,748.\n\nI should clarify the different definitions of Tokyo's population since there are several ways to measure it:\n- The 23 special wards (historic city of Tokyo): around 9+ million\n- Tokyo Metropolis (prefecture): about 14.27 million\n- Greater Tokyo Area (metropolitan area): around 36.9-37 million\n\nThe most commonly cited figure for \"Tokyo's population\" is usually the Greater Tokyo Area (the metropolitan region), which is the most populous metro area in the world.\n","sequence_number":598}

